<h2 id="Syntax" name="Syntax">Syntax</h2>
<pre class="syntaxbox"><a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax" title="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax">Formal syntax</a>: <code><a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/CSS_values_syntax#syntax-br-width" title="&lt;length&gt; | thin | medium | thick">&lt;br-width&gt;</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Double_bar" title="Double bar: the two entities are optional, and may appear in any order.">||</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/CSS_values_syntax#syntax-br-style" title="none | hidden | dotted | dashed | solid | double | groove | ridge | inset | outset">&lt;br-style&gt;</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Double_bar" title="Double bar: the two entities are optional, and may appear in any order.">||</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/color" title="">&lt;color&gt;</a></code>
</pre>
<h3 id="Values">Values</h3>
<dl><dt>
  <code>&lt;br-width&gt; </code></dt>
 <dd>
  See <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-bottom-width" title="The border-bottom-width CSS property sets the width of the bottom border of a box."><code>border-bottom-width</code></a>.</dd>
 <dt>
  <code>&lt;br-style&gt; </code></dt>
 <dd>
  See <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-bottom-style" title="The border-bottom-style CSS property sets the line style of the bottom border of a box."><code>border-bottom-style</code></a>.</dd>
 <dt>
  <code>&lt;color&gt; </code></dt>
 <dd>
  See <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-bottom-color" title="The border-bottom-color CSS property sets the color of the bottom border of an element. Note that in many cases the shorthand CSS properties border-color or border-bottom are more convenient and preferable."><code>border-bottom-color</code></a>.</dd>
</dl>